{"pageContext":{"html":"<p><a href=\"ctf=trend-micro-ctf-2015\"></a>\n<a href=\"type=prog\"></a>\n<a href=\"tags=\"></a>\n<a href=\"tools=PIL\"></a>\n<a href=\"techniques=\"></a></p>\n<h1>Click on the different color (prog-100)</h1>\n<p>Problem statement is straightforward. We are given a square grid:</p>\n<p><a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/40e0a03f1515e43afa7ad346d2a439da/4f4f8/squares.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 403px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 100%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    ></span>\n    <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"Squares\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/40e0a03f1515e43afa7ad346d2a439da/4f4f8/squares.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/40e0a03f1515e43afa7ad346d2a439da/5715d/squares.png 180w,\n/static/40e0a03f1515e43afa7ad346d2a439da/bedf2/squares.png 360w,\n/static/40e0a03f1515e43afa7ad346d2a439da/4f4f8/squares.png 403w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 403px) 100vw, 403px\"\n      />\n  </span>\n  </a></p>\n<p>We have to click on the tile which has the odd color. After each such click, the grid gets larger and larger. Obviously, we need to automate this, so wrote down a <a href=\"bot.py\">quick script</a>, and let it play for a few minutes. After our bot plays for about 80 levels, we get the flag:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>TMCTF{U must have R0807 3Y3s!}</p>\n</blockquote>"}}